Citations
Date: 20/4/1920
Source: NZ Journal of Agriculture
Author:
Vol / Page: 210
Edition:
Quote: The fruit should be carefully picked into a suitable picking-bag, and from thence equally carefully into the orchard picking-box, which should be well made and perfectly smooth on the inside. Picking-boxes when full should be handled as carefully as possible.
